name: Saddleback at Santa Rita Ranch
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Highly rated
amenities.description: Highly rated school district with new on-site schools

amenities.name: Conveniently located
amenities.description: Conveniently located near Lake Georgetown, providing great access to boat, ski, fish, and camp.

amenities.name: Close proximity
amenities.description: Close proximity to Garey Park, a 525-acre public park that includes nature-themed playgrounds, 28-feature splash pad, zip lines, and more.

amenities.name: Green Park
amenities.description: The Green Park featuring basketball court, fitness zone and green spaces

amenities.name: Children's splash
amenities.description: Children's splash pad and slide pool with 18 foot water slides

amenities.name: Ranch House
amenities.description: The Ranch House amenity center with outdoor seating, lounge area with fireplace, and ample space for social events

amenities.name: Game area
amenities.description: Game area for horseshoes and washers, with gas grills and large children's playscape
